<subSubSection pageId="147" pageNumber="545" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="147.[1388,2594,1361,1977]" pageId="147" pageNumber="545">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1388,1629,1668,1701]" pageId="147" pageNumber="545">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
Burrows thought to have represented Stuhlmann’s Golden Mole (Chrysochloris stuhlmanni fosteri) are now thought to represent feeding holes probably dug by this species on Mount Elgon.
</paragraph>
